						<img alt="" src="https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/872509ac255c6d14b3b9608f4ea89e26?s=68&amp;d=mm&amp;r=g" srcset="https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/872509ac255c6d14b3b9608f4ea89e26?s=136&amp;d=mm&amp;r=g 2x" class="avatar avatar-68 photo" height="68" width="68" loading="lazy" decoding="async">						<b class="fn">ania majdali</b> <span class="says">says:</span>					</div><!-- .comment-author -->

					<div class="comment-metadata">
						<a href="https://billmuehlenberg.com/2007/05/21/abortion-and-moral-relativism/#comment-32916"><time datetime="2007-10-02T14:14:46+10:00">Oct 2, 2007 at 2:14 pm</time></a>					</div><!-- .comment-metadata -->

									</footer><!-- .comment-meta -->

				<div class="comment-content">
					<p>Suuz,</p>
<p>You’re all for freedom of choice and women’s rights. Well if women have the right to abort their babies, we have the right to oppose it.</p>
<p>It’s not as simple as ‘her life, her choice’. It’s not her life, it’s her child’s life. She just gets to choose whether or not she wants to end it.</p>
<p>Ania Majdali</p>
				</div><!-- .comment-content -->

							</article><!-- .comment-body -->
		</li><!-- #comment-## -->
		<li id="comment-56180" class="comment odd alt thread-odd thread-alt depth-1">
			<article id="div-comment-56180" class="comment-body">
				<footer class="comment-meta">
					<div class="comment-author vcard">
						<img alt="" src="https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/17cd5818b3b94481873a5b3d5e23bceb?s=68&amp;d=mm&amp;r=g" srcset="https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/17cd5818b3b94481873a5b3d5e23bceb?s=136&amp;d=mm&amp;r=g 2x" class="avatar avatar-68 photo" height="68" width="68" loading="lazy" decoding="async">						<b class="fn">Lars Munk Sørensen</b> <span class="says">says:</span>					</div><!-- .comment-author -->

					<div class="comment-metadata">
						<a href="https://billmuehlenberg.com/2007/05/21/abortion-and-moral-relativism/#comment-56180"><time datetime="2008-01-29T16:01:21+11:00">Jan 29, 2008 at 4:01 pm</time></a>					</div><!-- .comment-metadata -->

									</footer><!-- .comment-meta -->

				<div class="comment-content">
					<p>In my country, Denmark, a memorial park for the unborn victims of abortion has been ruled unlawful, because it offended the ethics of abortionists. But I believe that accepting abortion on grounds such as euthanasia (“It´s better for a child to be dead than to be adopted or live with unfit parents”) or pro-choice (“It is the mother´s body, not the child”) puts us on the same level as the Nazis killing “unfit humans”. However, the nazis were cruel, but honest. How can we critisize unfit dictators around the Third World, if we keep killing our own unborn babies?<br>
Lars Munk Sørensen, Denmark</p>
				</div><!-- .comment-content -->

							</article><!-- .comment-body -->
		</li><!-- #comment-## -->
		<li id="comment-56519" class="comment even thread-even depth-1">
			<article id="div-comment-56519" class="comment-body">
				<footer class="comment-meta">
					<div class="comment-author vcard">
						<img alt="" src="https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/17cd5818b3b94481873a5b3d5e23bceb?s=68&amp;d=mm&amp;r=g" srcset="https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/17cd5818b3b94481873a5b3d5e23bceb?s=136&amp;d=mm&amp;r=g 2x" class="avatar avatar-68 photo" height="68" width="68" loading="lazy" decoding="async">						<b class="fn">Lars Munk Sørensen</b> <span class="says">says:</span>					</div><!-- .comment-author -->

					<div class="comment-metadata">
						<a href="https://billmuehlenberg.com/2007/05/21/abortion-and-moral-relativism/#comment-56519"><time datetime="2008-01-31T16:32:34+11:00">Jan 31, 2008 at 4:32 pm</time></a>					</div><!-- .comment-metadata -->

									</footer><!-- .comment-meta -->

				<div class="comment-content">
					<p>An unborn child is conceived the moments the sperm penetrates the egg. After that, it will evolve until it is a grown old person who dies a natural death. Any humanly planned deadline, before which it is lawful to kill it, is arbitrary: 5 seconds after that line, it is murder to kill it. 5 seconds before, its lawful in my “civilized” country of Denmark …<br>
Lars Munk Sørensen</p>
				</div><!-- .comment-content -->

							</article><!-- .comment-body -->
		</li><!-- #comment-## -->
		<li id="comment-96114" class="comment odd alt thread-odd thread-alt depth-1">
			<article id="div-comment-96114" class="comment-body">
				<footer class="comment-meta">
					<div class="comment-author vcard">
						<img alt="" src="https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/1213f7bbb39ec57d7dc0f852ec9a2953?s=68&amp;d=mm&amp;r=g" srcset="https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/1213f7bbb39ec57d7dc0f852ec9a2953?s=136&amp;d=mm&amp;r=g 2x" class="avatar avatar-68 photo" height="68" width="68" loading="lazy" decoding="async">						<b class="fn">Tristan l</b> <span class="says">says:</span>					</div><!-- .comment-author -->

					<div class="comment-metadata">
						<a href="https://billmuehlenberg.com/2007/05/21/abortion-and-moral-relativism/#comment-96114"><time datetime="2008-08-19T18:23:50+10:00">Aug 19, 2008 at 6:23 pm</time></a>					</div><!-- .comment-metadata -->

									</footer><!-- .comment-meta -->

				<div class="comment-content">
					<p>Excellent post, spot on the mark.</p>
<p>@Suuz Tompkins.</p>
<p>“Mayor Giuliani, like yourself, is against abortion. He, like yourself, thinks its morally wrong, <b>he, unlike you, does not impose his opionion on the world and expect everyone to submit to his value system.</b> We can’t make everyone like what we like, value what we value, and do what we do. If a woman wants an abortion, its her life, its her choice. Not yours.”</p>
<p>The attitude of “morally neutral” (everyone make up their own mind) is self-defeating and incomprehensible. </p>
<p>You say that it is her choice, leave her alone. Yet then you tell others to abide with your moral choice, to leave everyone to their own choice. Inconsistent?</p>
<p>(And yes, the attitude “let everyone make up their own mind, to not force your opinions on others” IS forcing your opinion on others. People can make up their own opinion AS LONG AS it doesn’t affect me/others is forcing your opinion).</p>
<p>Tristan Ingle, Sydney</p>
				</div><!-- .comment-content -->

							</article><!-- .comment-body -->
		</li><!-- #comment-## -->
		<li id="comment-234923" class="comment even thread-even depth-1">
			<article id="div-comment-234923" class="comment-body">
				<footer class="comment-meta">
					<div class="comment-author vcard">
						<img alt="" src="https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/9c86555c9aeececb770dd80ea86cd112?s=68&amp;d=mm&amp;r=g" srcset="https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/9c86555c9aeececb770dd80ea86cd112?s=136&amp;d=mm&amp;r=g 2x" class="avatar avatar-68 photo" height="68" width="68" loading="lazy" decoding="async">						<b class="fn">Heather</b> <span class="says">says:</span>					</div><!-- .comment-author -->

					<div class="comment-metadata">
						<a href="https://billmuehlenberg.com/2007/05/21/abortion-and-moral-relativism/#comment-234923"><time datetime="2011-03-11T16:19:43+11:00">Mar 11, 2011 at 4:19 pm</time></a>					</div><!-- .comment-metadata -->

									</footer><!-- .comment-meta -->

				<div class="comment-content">
					<p>People attempting to justify taking the life of an innocent, unborn child frustrate me. By all accounts women do have a right to make choices with regard to their bodies. However, the choice about your body should begin with the choices that you make which put you in the position to even be contemplating an abortion. If you do not want to be pregnant then utilize birth control. Furthermore, if you are not willing to face the potential consequences of having sex, which, pregnancy does pose as a possibility, then maybe you should not be having sex. You want to have choices and be in control of your body, then take control and make responsible choices with your body and then you avoid unwanted pregnancies. Lastly, if a woman should have rights and should be able to make choices regarding her body, why then does the unborn baby, whose voice cannot yet be heard, have no rights to their body? The unborn baby’s heart starts beating between 18 and 25 days after conception, well before a woman even knows that she is pregnant. It has little arms, legs, hands, feet and all organs are there. It is a whole little human being, who only needs to grow and be given the opportunity to be, to live, and to fulfill its purpose in life……<br>
Heather Davis</p>
				</div><!-- .comment-content -->

							</article><!-- .comment-body -->
